</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="124.[667,1194,213,1759]" lastBlockId="125.[128,654,1174,1759]" lastPageId="125" lastPageNumber="125" pageId="124" pageNumber="124">
Variation was noted in the number and size of the short, parallel apical spines and the intensity of apical serration in the medial process of the right paramere from 
<specimenCount pageId="124" pageNumber="124" type="generic">six specimens</specimenCount>
across 
<collectingRegion box="[919,1007,1708,1729]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="124" pageNumber="124">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1113,1193,1708,1730]" country="Mexico" name="Puebla" pageId="124" pageNumber="124">Puebla</collectingRegion>
(fig. 28A–H). Little variation was noted in the endosomal spicule and left paramere, all having the form shown in figure 29A, C.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
